choices.text:
Put together a healthy meal plan for me for this week.  I can't have dairy, garlic, honey, almonds, pistachios, or cashews
Sure! Here is a sample meal plan that meets your dietary restrictions:
Breakfast: Scrambled eggs with spinach and tomatoes (no dairy) served with whole wheat toast 
Lunch: Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, carrots, cucumbers, cherry tomatoes, and balsamic vinaigrette dressing (no garlic or honey) served with a side of quinoa 
Dinner: Baked salmon with roasted sweet potato and asparagus (no almonds, pistachios, or cashews) served with steamed broccoli 
Snacks: Apple slices with almond butter, celery sticks with hummus, or carrot sticks with ranch dressing.
